{
  "texts": [
    "The integral energy contributions closely follow the ground truth from DNS, with only minor uniform deviations and no significant outliers.",
    "The PF-VcPINNs and the baseline model VcNet exhibit similar temporal trends, with only minor differences.",
    "Table S7 details the relative L 1 and L 2 errors of the energy contributions eval- uated across the validation dataset for the prediction by VoF-VcPINNs, PF-VcPINNs, and VcNet.",
    "As can be seen in Figure S11, the potential energy E g is predicted consistently well by VoF-VcPINNs, which is reflected in the low relative L 2 error of RL 2 E g = 3.0%.",
    "PF-VcPINNs achieve the most accurate results with RL 2 E g = 1.7%."
  ]
}